article.headline: Miami (FL) 89, Stetson 64
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Brian Asbury scored 18 points and Jimmy Graham grabbed 13 rebounds in 21 minutes to lead Miami to an 89-64 victory over Stetson on Saturday. Asbury was 7-of-9 from the field, including 4-of-6 on 3-pointers. He had six rebounds and six assists. Miami (7-4) took a 16-3 lead and didn't allow Stetson (3-7) to get closer than nine points the rest of the way. The Hurricanes led by as many as 30 in the closing minutes. Miami shot 59 percent from the field while holding Stetson to 37 percent. Jack McClinton and Denis Clemente both scored 13 points for Miami, while Raymond Hicks added 12 and Anthony Harris 11. Eric Diaz led Stetson with 11 points and Garfield Blair and J.J. Hirst both scored 10.
